ion of overeating. After a couple of hours grazing around the various food stalls I waddled back to the hotel for a little siesta to sleep it off.\n\nOn Boxing Day all the businesses were back to normal so I was able to deal with some chores like doing my laundry etc before meeting up with a few guys from the bike co-op for a few beers in the evening. Esteban - the guy who runs the co-op also insisted we try pulque, a drink similar in strength to beer made from fermented agave. I wasnt a huge fan as in addition to a strange sour taste, it also had almost the exact same consistency as snot which was a thought I just couldnt get out of my head as I politely forced it down.\n\nAfter a good few days rest over the festive period Im ready to head further south into Mexico. Im not sure of my exact route but I think the general plan will be to aim to skirt around the south of Mexico City (I dont fancy riding the bike across another megacity after Los Angeles) and then see where we go from there. Hasta luego!	Tequila, rain soakings and mechanical issues	mexico	climbing-inland	2023-02-19 20:02:42.729	2023-02-19 20:10:10	2023-02-19 20:10:09.996	1	1	2019-12-27
